Greater Middlesex Conference Tournament 
South Plainfield 3, Sayreville 3, (6-5 PKs): Jacob Villacres tallied one goal and one assist as sixth-seeded South Plainfield (12-6-1) won 6-5 in penalty kicks. Richard Marcovecchio and Deshai Smith also scored. Jake Hoffman chipped in an assist. Nick Plate and Chris Kuberiet combined for eight saves. For No. 11 Sayreville (8-7-3), Kevin Sousa had one goal and one assist. Louis Brooks and Zachary Colgan also scored. Tyle Gates and Matt Barbosa each tallied one assist. Mohil Trivedi made seven saves. 
Monroe 4, South River 3 (OT): Alex Fernandez and Matt Hoyt each tallied a goal and an assist to lead third-seeded Monroe (14-2-1). Zach Hroch and Ryan McCabe also scored. Nark Miranda, Jonathan Franco and Ian Sawicki all scored for No. 14 South River (9-8-1). Kevin Mendez and Ryan Farrell each had an assist. 
Metuchen 3, Spotswood 2: Ryan Josell scored twice, including the game-winner and tallied an assist to lead seventh-seeded Metuchen (13-4). Cameron O’Connell recorded a goal and an assist. For No. 10 Spotswood (11-6), Andrew Picado and John Reyes scored. Ed Kovalski had an assist. 
South Brunswick 6, J.P. Steven 1: Keiler Knapp and Pat Grudnick each scored twice to power top-seeded South Brunswick (14-3). Christos Lolas and Jermaine Small also scored. For No. 16 J.P. Stevens (6-13-1), Sayak Ghosh scored. 
Old Bridge 3, East Brunswick Tech 0: Joel Quist, Tyler Mazza and Christian McCartney all scored to lead ninth-seeded Old Bridge (9-9). Mark Akselrud made four saves. For eighth-seeded East Brunswick Tech (12-3), Troy Bello made 10 stops. 
St. Joseph 2, Bishop Ahr 1: Chris Talaska scored and Bishop Ahr scored an own goal to lead fifth-seeded St. Joseph (10-8-1). Luke Roche scored on an assist from Dylan Cruz for the 12th-seeded Trojans (10-6-1). Read or Share this story: http://mycj.co/1LURE5E TOP VIDEOS
